## Progress
- Attempted to share WorldModel across agents — REVERTED
  - Each agent uses agent-relative coordinates (not true global)
  - Sharing causes agents to navigate to wrong positions
  - Previous sessions noted this as a bug but it's actually by design
- Deep analysis of 0-score wipeouts found ROOT CAUSE:
  - Gear station contention: all 5 aligners + 2 miners rush to stations at step 1
  - Hub only has 24 of each element. Gear costs: aligner=6, miner=6
  - 5 aligners + 3 miners = 8 gears × 6 avg = 48 resources needed, but hub only has 24 each
  - Many agents arrive at station but can't get gear (hub depleted)
  - Stuck agents burn HP waiting, never recover
  - On bad maps, starter policy also scores 0 (map-dependent)
- Coordinate system: agents start at different spawn points with different (0,0) origins
  - Bootstrap hub offsets are per-agent: {0: (0,3), 1: (0,2), 2: (3,0), ...}
  - Entity global_x/y are relative to each agent's spawn
- Key insight for improvement:
  - Don't rush all gear at once — stagger gear acquisition
  - More miners initially to build economy before aligners gear up
  - Align only in safe zones (away from ship scramble radius)
